      "comment": "DARK FURY (3) has been out of the placings in two runs since a break, the latest when fourth, beaten 7 lengths, over 1207m at this track (Dirt) after she was in the firing line on the turn. Has never been out of the placings at the third run in and is expected to feature in the finish. ST ALBANS RAID (1) finished out of the money two starts back then she got a long way back and was beaten 10 lengths when seventh in a 1609m contest at this track three weeks ago. Suitably placed so anticipating a big run this time. BALLS IN UR COURT (8) was comfortably accounted for when eighth last time out over 1207m at this track, beaten 22 lengths. That followed a win at this track at the previous outing. Perfectly placed and is sure to take a ton of beating. SICILIAN GRANDMA (5) is having her first run since winning by 0.8 lengths six weeks ago over 1207m at this track. Has transferred to the Tom H Swearingen stable over the break. Has found the right race and is worth including.",
